0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Daley has complained about the food hall in the Olympic village, saying it 'gets busy' and urging officials to find a way around the problem.\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4050, \"end\": 4059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2374407123001253e-68, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Offering an insight into what goes on behind the scenes in an interview withGQ,Daley said: \\\"The village itself is actually quite great.\", \"from\": 4197, \"to\": 4332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The only thing is the food hall gets busy.\", \"from\": 4334, \"to\": 4377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully they will figure that out because as the Games go on it's just going to get busier and busier.\\\"\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Iga Swiatek will not be playing in the women's singles final after suffering a shock defeat to Zheng Qinwen of China.\", \"from\": 4485, \"to\": 4602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4485, \"end\": 4488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.973356322228615e-22, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 4580, \"end\": 4592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zheng Qinwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\"}, {\"begin\": 4596, \"end\": 4601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6782558702547745, \"rank\": 0.39007531025577014, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's top-ranked female playerrefused to shake the umpire's handfollowing her 6-2 7-5 defeat and later walked away from an interview to cry.\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although she still has a shot at the bronze medal, Swiatek had made no secret of her desire to win Olympic gold prior to her surprise exit.\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her conqueror Zheng will face either Donna Vekic or Anna Schmiedlova in the final on Saturday.\", \"from\": 4893, \"to\": 4987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4907, \"end\": 4912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5366592128212654e-16, \"text\": \"Zheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\"}, {\"begin\": 4930, \"end\": 4941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999999518913694, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donna Vekic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 4945, \"end\": 4949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"score\": 0.9999920015772392, \"rank\": 7.998486802344358e-06, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There has been a dramatic twist in the Olympic sailing with the men's skiff medal race being abandoned.\", \"from\": 4989, \"to\": 5092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was stopped a few moments ago after a huge shift in the wind direction, presumably because officials decided it would give an unfair advantage to some competitiors.\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB duo James Peters and Fynn Sterritt were sixth at the time of the stoppage.\", \"from\": 5263, \"to\": 5345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5275, \"end\": 5280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9999994528799694, \"rank\": 5.470950930926866e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are waiting to find out when the race will get back underway.\", \"from\": 5346, \"to\": 5410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"BBC commentator Niall Myant said: \\\"I have never seen that in a medal race at the Olympic level.\", \"from\": 5412, \"to\": 5507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5412, \"end\": 5415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9999789839801595, \"rank\": 2.099798423112085e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 5428, \"end\": 5433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Rafferty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5209597973577114e-29, \"text\": \"Niall\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Rafferty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Rafferty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can only imagine it's because the breeze has drifted so dramatically the committee have decided it's unfair so they have abandoned the race.\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quite the moment.\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That would have been a really hard decision.\", \"from\": 5672, \"to\": 5716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They obviously felt that it was unworkable, it was pushing boats forward that should not have been there and they have decided to let this one go.\\\"\", \"from\": 5717, \"to\": 5864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinese swimmer Pan Zhanle has been accused of cheating by a rival coach after smashing the world record for the men's 100 metre freestyle.\", \"from\": 5868, \"to\": 6007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5868, \"end\": 5875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998850515881311, \"rank\": 8.646847423880396e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 19-year-old broke his own record by almost half a second as he finished an entire body length ahead of Australian rival Kyle Chalmers.\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6116, \"end\": 6126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999816124053511, \"rank\": 1.83871736280106e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 6133, \"end\": 6146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyle Chalmers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pan's incredible swim prompted a furious reaction from Brett Hawke, who coaches Chalmers.\", \"from\": 6149, \"to\": 6238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6204, \"end\": 6215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brett Hawke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"It is not humanly possible to beat that field by a body length.\", \"from\": 6240, \"to\": 6313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not care what you say.\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is not a race thing, this is not against any one particular person or nation, this is just what I see and what I know.\", \"from\": 6343, \"to\": 6467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not real.\", \"from\": 6468, \"to\": 6484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You do not beat that field.\", \"from\": 6486, \"to\": 6514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kyle Chalmers, David Popovici, Jack Alexy.\", \"from\": 6515, \"to\": 6557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6515, \"end\": 6528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyle Chalmers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\"}, {\"begin\": 6520, \"end\": 6535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chalmers, David\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chalmers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chalmers\"}, {\"begin\": 6520, \"end\": 6535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chalmers, David\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q